mts.s:
From your WBS and Gantt Chart, estimate how much this project would cost if you were employed.  Use figures presented in class.
 
State in 1-2 paragraphs how you would control for quality.  What measurements would you take in order to make a case that this project was of high quality?
 
List the risks involved in doing this project at each step.  Accompany each with a statement about how you would mitigate risk.
 
Name the file TEAMNAMECost and submit it by putting it in the Google Docs folder you have permitted to us.

1.0 Initiating
1.1 Establish communication with CADC members
	1.1.1 Share initial project proposal with members
	1.1.2 Obtain permission to alter their website, gather information, etc.
1.2 Prepare project Business Case
1.3 Hold project kickoff meeting
	1.3.1 Notify others about the project and how everything might progress
1.4 Elicit Requirements from CADC board members
2.0 Planning
2.1 Hold team planning meeting
	2.1.1 Determine roles for all team members
	2.1.2 Determine initial requirements for creating a website
2.2 Prepare Team Communication Covenant
	2.21 Have group sign off with their name and contact information (resources)
2.3 Prepare scope statement
2.4 Prepare WBS
2.5 Prepare schedule
2.5.1 Determine task durations
2.5.2 Determine task dependencies
2.5.3 Create Gantt chart draft
2.5.4 Review and finalize Gantt chart
2.6 Identify, discuss, and prioritize risks
3.0 Website Setup
3.1 Gather resources
	3.1.1 Collect CADC member database
	3.1.2 Collect multimedia files
3.2 Choose program to support HTML and CSS coding
3.3 Secure Domain name
	3.3.1 Research how to buy domain names
	3.3.2 Create a usable url name
	3.3.3 Purchase domain name
4.0 Website Creation
	4.1 Design website content
4.1.1 Create wireframe
4.1.2 Create prototype designs
4.1.3 Designate sections
4.2 Rebrand CADC
	4.2.1 Create new CADC logo
	4.2.2 Reinvent website graphics and colors
4.3 Develop website
4.3.1 Construct home page and shell for interior pages
4.3.2 Distribute content in appropriate pages
4.3.3 Integrate Social Media
4.3.4 Integrate Google Applications
4.3.5 Implement user-requested features
5.0 Status Updates
5.1 Team Update Meeting
	5.1.1 Reassess team roles
	5.1.2 Review struggles and accomplishments
	5.1.3 Reevaluate reachable goals and desired functionality
5.2 Quality and Risk assessment
	5.2.1 Determine if incomplete functionality is completable within time frame
	5.2.2 Reassess if site functionality is as originally planned	
6.0 Analysis and Testing
	6.1 Debug site
		6.1.1 Check for browser compatibility
		6.1.2 Test navigation
		6.1.3 Test interactive elements
	6.2 Conduct Usability tests with CADC Members
	6.3 Make adjustments to site
		6.3.1 Tailor to any suggestions made from usability tests
		6.3.1 Add additional content and functionality
6.4 CADC site promotion
	6.4.1 Unveil finished website to CADC
6.5 CADC site roll-out
	6.5.1 Establish target date
	6.5.2 Make site live
7.0 Closing
7.1 Project benefits measurement
	7.1.1 Compare our site with previous site
7.2 Prepare final project report
7.3 Prepare final project presentation
7.4 Teach CADC board how to use and update site
	7.4.1 Create simple manual for maintenance and use of website
7.5 Lessons learned
